THE FACTS

+ Prominent 1,564sqm* commercial 1 zoned landholding

+ Existing double storey commercial building of 1,267sqm* with nine tenancies in place

+ $267,000pa* passing income – currently 90%* leased

+ Imposing retail strip frontage of 33.5m* with dual street access & 36 car spaces at rear

+ Permit approval for a mixed-use development comprising 52 apartments plus two ground floor retail spaces

+ Architecturally designed by esteemed architects, Rothelowman

THE LOCATION

+ Positioned in a thriving retail & dining precinct, surrounded by an array of trendy dining options, popular fresh food market & wine bars

+ Close to popular Allnut Park (350m*), Brighton Public Golf Course (1.3km*) and only 4km* to the famed Brighton Beach & Bathing Boxes

+ Premium education facilities nearby including Bentleigh West Primary School (600m*), Roseberry Early Learning Centre (100m*) & zoned for McKinnon Secondary College (3km*)

+ Positioned 12.5km* south east of the Melbourne CBD with direct access via recently reconstructed Bentleigh Train Station (300m*)

PUBLIC TENDER NOW CLOSED

CBRE Melbourne Strip Retail Investments are proud to present to the market, 496 Centre Road, Bentleigh being offered for sale via Public On-Site Auction Friday 19th May at 12:30pm.

•Strategically positioned on a high exposure, triple fronted allotment

•An irreplaceable 192sqm* landholding with combined frontage of 44.7m*

•Join the likes of national retailers Nando’s, Dominos, Subway, Brumbys, Coles, BWS, Woolworths, Bakers Delight and many more

•Nearby the newly updated Bentleigh Station and conveniently serviced by over 200* free council car spaces

•Offered with vacant possession providing the ultimate flexibility to occupy, invest or develop

•Located within the prestigious suburb of Bentleigh, with a median house price of $1,520,000 (Bentleigh has experienced 54% capital growth since January 2014)
